{"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"fragments":[{"text":"overlayBounds","kind":"identifier"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Property","externalID":"c:objc(pl)MLNOverlay(py)overlayBounds","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"overlayBounds","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"overlayBounds","modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"property"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"occ","url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/overlayBounds"},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"@property"},{"kind":"text","text":" ("},{"kind":"keyword","text":"nonatomic"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"readonly"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@MLNCoordinateBounds","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"MLNCoordinateBounds","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNCoordinateBounds"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"overlayBounds"},{"kind":"text","text":";"}],"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["occ"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This property contains the smallest rectangle that completely encompasses the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"overlay. Implementers of this protocol must set this area when implementing","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"their overlay class, and after setting it, you must not change it.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If this overlay spans the antimeridian, its bounds may extend west of −180 degrees","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"longitude or east of 180 degrees longitude. For example, an overlay covering the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Pacific Ocean from Tokyo to San Francisco might have a bounds extending","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"from (35.68476, −220.24257) to (37.78428, −122.41310).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/overlaybounds"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"abstract":[{"text":"The cooordinate rectangle that encompasses the overlay. (required) (read-only)","type":"text"}],"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNCoordinateBounds":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNCoordinateBounds"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlncoordinatebounds","title":"MLNCoordinateBounds","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"A rectangular area as measured on a two-dimensional map projection.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNCoordinateBounds"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay/overlayBounds":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The cooordinate rectangle that encompasses the overlay. (required) (read-only)"}],"title":"overlayBounds","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/overlaybounds","role":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"overlayBounds","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/overlayBounds","kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling.","type":"text"}],"title":"MapLibre"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol defines a specific type of annotation that represents"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"both a point and an area on a map. Overlay objects are essentially data objects"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that contain the geographic data needed to represent the map area. Overlays can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"take the form of a polyline or polygon."}],"title":"MLNOverlay","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"MLNOverlay","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol"}}}